vietnamese were in the first group to return dec 1 although 111 
had signed up interest in the voluntary program also is lagging 
although the total number of vietnamese in hong kong declined by 
several thousand over the last year the decrease has been among 
boat people who already had been granted refugee status and a 
chance to settle in the west 
people who await screening on their qualifications as refugees 
plus those who flunked the process have increased from 43702 in 
1989 to 43949 as of dec 3 also 2684 babies were born in the 
camps giving the boat people one of the highest birth rates in the 
world 
these increases are intolerable leeks said what happens 
if theres another mass exodus next year 
