voter defeat of a government overhaul designed to 
help minorities get elected to city council means a federal judge 
is free to impose a new setup on the city 
residents on saturday rejected by 369 votes a measure under 
which 14 council members would be elected from districts and the 
mayor would be elected from the city as a whole the vote was 
45255 in favor and 45624 against 
under the current system instituted in 1975 eight members are 
elected from districts and three others including the mayor are 
elected from the city at large 
with the plans defeat us district judge jerry buchmeyer 
could institute the same plan or a similar one and call a city 
council election in may mayor annette strauss said the judge 
indicated he could rule as early as january 
supporters said the plan would have helped ease racial 
inequities that make it difficult for minorities to get elected 
opponents said the system would have resegregated dallas they 
backed a plan calling for 10 candidates to be elected by district 
