the 175member party central committee generally meets in the 
early autumn it was expected to do so this year to approve new 
five and tenyear plans for the economy to take effect on jan 1 
when the old plans expire 
but intense backstage wrangling over the pace of economic reform 
and development priorities has stalled the drafting of plans 
li said the central committee will meet at the end of december 
