be the only agenda item dispelling rumors that several ministerial 
changes also will be discussed 
the act of convening a central committee meeting indicates that 
some basic agreement on economic policy has been reached the 
chinese traditionally try to avoid open debate at such meetings and 
keep arguments to informal settings 
officials have been arguing about a host of issues including 
how much control the central government should have over the 
economy how much revenue provinces should give the center and 
whether stateset prices should be raised or freed from control 
the economic arguments cloak a struggle over ideology and power 
chinas power broker of the past decade senior leader deng 
xiaoping has lost prestige since endorsing the army attack on 
