contributions 
paul carpenter stood silently when us district judge edward 
garcia sentenced him declining an offer to speak 
carpenter a silverhaired 62yearold democrat from suburban 
los angeles was convicted in september of racketeering extortion 
and conspiracy the charges followed an undercover operation at the 
state capital in the sting an fbi agent posing as a businessman 
paid carpenter 20000 in campaign contributions to get a bill 
through the legislature 
at carpenters trial other instances were cited of his shaking 
down lobbyists for campaign money 
carpenter who must surrender to authorities by jan 7 was also 
ordered to repay 20000 he received from an fbi undercover agent 
in the sting operation 
its a case of proven acceptance of bribery money and 
extortion of money in the form of political contributions said 
the judge who called the evidence against carpenter 
overwhelming 
