<TEXT>
lawmakers in the supreme soviet voted monday to 
give investors and labor organizers more legal protection 
throughout the soviet union 
the legislation dealt mainly with the principles of a market 
economy and did not address issues of currency convertibility or 
property ownership nor the dismantling of a state bureaucracy that 
often saddles investors with red tape 
the supreme soviet approved general principles of investment 
policy that guarantees equal rights for all investors 
irrespective of property forms tass reported the act is aimed 
at forming markettype investment relations and stepping up 
entrepreneurial activities in the country 
the state news agency said investors under the new legislation 
must be reimbursed for any losses incurred by actions of state 
bodies violating their rights 
the legislature later adopted a law on trade unions that 
provides for the independence of trade unions from government 
economic and political bodies and their complete material and 
financial independence tass reported it gave few other details 
the law on labor unions comes two months after 900 soviet coal 
miners meeting in the ukraine established their own independent 
union and set up a governing structures that rejected state 
involvement 
for most of the soviet unions 73year history labor unions 
were outlawed on the theory that the ruling communist party 
embodied interests of workers as the leading party of the workers 
state 
