before they participated in crucial meetings with thrift 
regulators on keatings behalf in 1987 other subjects of the 
ethics probe are sens donald w riegle jr dmich john glenn 
dohio and alan cranston dcalif 
before stevens testified former us customs commissioner 
william von raab told the committee that senators often intervened 
with him on behalf of constituents 
von raab testified for sen dennis deconcini one of five 
senators under investigation for intervening with thrift regulators 
on behalf of charles h keating jr 
asked by committee member warren rudman rnh where you 
would draw that line of unacceptable conduct by senators von 
raab replied if someone tried to bribe me 
deconcini was the only one of the five senators present as von 
raab testified that lawmakers often asked him to grant waivers for 
constituents and to reconsider regulations 
the committee held its 15th day of hearings on the relationship 
between the five senators and keating who with associates 
contributed 13 million to the lawmakers campaigns and causes 
the five senators asked thrift regulators in 1987 to reconsider 
a regulation limiting risky investments such as those undertaken by 
keatings failing lincoln savings and loan of irvine calif 
lincoln was seized in april 1989 at a potential cost to 
taxpayers of more than 2 billion 
regulators testified that deconcini sought to negotiate a waiver 
of the rule for lincoln and used the word we to indicate he was 
speaking for the other senators 
regulators contend that deconcini improperly negotiated on 
keatings behalf at that meeting 
von raab said he had never been confronted by lawmakers under 
the exact circumstances as those faced by banking regulators when 
the five senators met with them in april 1987 
committee special counsel robert s bennett noted that those 
meetings were held without aides on behalf of a single constituent 
lincoln which already had been found in violation of the rule 
on direct investments 
all you have said is sen deconcini is a friend f yours and 
all of your dealings with him have been honorable and 
