calls herself the villain of the piece shes actually the victim 
putupon by a sleazy guy who picks her up in a bar following her 
on stage is a tightrope walker jayne haynes named fifi and her 
human cannonball of a husband omar graham beckel who walks around 
with what looks like an old pot on his head 
they are best friends with an unemployed actor named austin 
jake weber who saves the girl after she is humiliated in the bar 
shes tormented by that creep skip suddut who smears petroleum 
jelly on her head she also has a thing for salad oil but thats 
not revealed until the second act the first act ends with a bubble 
bath given to the girl by her rescuer at least it quiets the 
audience 
act 2 is a mad hatterstyle dinner for the four friends during 
the meal austin waxes murkily about life for some reason also 
not entirely clear the actor walks offstage and then returns 
naked to lecture the audience on confronting their own fears he 
certainly doesnt have any of his own being able to stand there in 
the buff and remember all his lines 
the actors are cheerful and enthusiastic in their portrayals of 
weirdness and tripplehorn and weber deserve medals for baring more 
than their souls but the big funk remains a collection of odd 
portraits and pictures rather than a play it doesnt say much when 
the most arresting moment on stage is not anything the actors say 
but rather an oozing familysize jar of vaseline spilling to the 
floor of the stage 
