the florida department of revenue 
expects its 6 percent newspaper tax to raise 257 million in the 
next year the states press association hopes to kill the sales 
tax in court first 
newspapers had to begin paying the sales tax dec 9 
the tax formerly applied only to magazines magazine publishers 
petitioned the courts for an exemption but the state supreme court 
on may 31 ruled that the best way to remedy the situation was to 
tax newspapers 
the court turned down a motion dec 6 to delay the tax while the 
florida press association appeals to the us supreme court 
meanwhile newspaper companies are collecting the tax some said 
they would absorb it on box sales and others planned to raise 
percopy prices 
dick shelton executive director of the state press association 
said tennessee arkansas iowa and several other states have sales 
tax cases pending before the us supreme court and that he 
expects the florida case to be consolidated with the others 
