<DOCNO> AP901210-0208 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
 
rome ap if romes mosque is a mute symbol of 
christianmoslem harmony then paolo portoghesi is a living symbol 
portoghesi a roman catholic and seventhgeneration native of 
this city of popes is the leader of the team of architects that 
designed romes first moslem house of worship 
this has been the most important project of my career says 
portoghesi 59 one of italys most prominent architects and a 
wellknown rome socialite and socialist party figure 
the mosque is not only a symbol of islams important place in 
the world he says but it is also a sign of the new 
catholicism one that is not rigidly closed to other religions but 
is tolerant and open to dialogue 
portoghesi is not new to the world of islam he has traveled and 
studied extensively in moslem countries he teaches islamic 
architecture at the university of rome and has designed 
stilltobebuilt mosques in jordan and sudan 
when they had the international competition for the rome 
mosque i participated with enthusiasm because it was a subject i 
was familiar with he says 
the commission of islamic experts judging the designs eventually 
narrowed the choice to two architects portoghesi and sami mousawi 
of iraq in the end the two architects were assigned to merge 
their designs into one 
the result is what portoghesi describes as a blend of islamic 
and roman tradition 
we chose forms of architecture which express the dialogue 
between the two cultures he says the intertwined arches are 
typical of islam but they also were used centuries ago by francesco 
borromini all the material we used such as travertine is typical 
of rome 
even the garden he says will harmonize the two civilizations 
pine trees of rome and palm trees of the desert 
portoghesi takes more pride in the mosques artistic traits than 
in its imposing size 
