to approach it its just a much more complex city its 
impersonalized its complicated its fastpaced nolte said 
and i certainly do need a certain kind of pace when im not in 
the actual process of doing a film i need a pace where i can think 
a little 
thats what he gets in west virginias capital a compact city 
snuggled along the snaking kanawha river and sheltered by the 
appalachian foothills 
although he owns a house in malibu calif nolte retreats to 
charleston where his wife becky and a previous wife sharon 
haddad both grew up and he can avoid hobnobbing with the film 
crowd 
to nolte living in new york or los angeles inevitably forces 
actors to compete against each other to prove acting ability and 
commercial clout 
one of the reasons i live in west virginia is to stay away 
from that rather than living in one of the film centers that 
constantly talk about this film succeeding and that film and 
whether this guy was good and that guy was good he said i 
like to get away from that judgmental kind of thinking 
the relaxed lifestyle of charleston also suits nolte who grew 
up in a similar atmosphere in omaha neb and ames iowa 
i play golf and i hike and stuff like that said nolte who 
played football while bouncing through five different colleges in 
the early 1960s he also loves to fish 
its also easier for nolte the father to get out in charleston 
with his 4yearold son brawley 
i have my son up in new york city and i get him outside the 
hotel for a walk in the park and its fairly intense nolte 
said here i can take him out let him run on the street play 
in the backyard and the woods in la if i want to take him 
to the park i have to get him in a car and go on a freeway thats 
the most traveled road in the world 
nolte 49 has found himself on some lesstraveled roads as an 
actor which he became after abandoning college in 1962 
he started hanging out at a pasadena calif theater with an 
actor friend to meet girls he says and got hooked on the 
stage a decade of touring the midwest landed him back in los 
angeles in 1973 where he finally hit it big in 1976 with the tv 
miniseries rich man poor man 
