cranberries 
so often we limit these popping beauties to a sweet sauce for 
turkey yet cranberries with their sharp bright taste combine with 
many ingredients 
for example when you combine cranberry cocktail juice with 
orange sherbert ginger ale and club soda and float oranges in the 
punch bowl you have a not too tart not too sweet punch for the 
whole family of course you can also add spirits 
maybe you havent thought of cranberries in soup before but 
they are wonderful as cranberry borscht a super entree for a 
holiday occasion an unusual cranberry dish is a cranberry salsa to 
spice up any roast turkey ham pork tenderloin 
by the way any cranberry sauce recipe can be spooned over a 
roast for the last halfhour of baking to make a lovely glaze and 
for the crowning touch for dessert cranberry jubilee flambeed 
with brandy and served over ice cream 
dont forget to string cranberries along with popcorn for 
homemade decorations for the tree and store some packages in your 
freezer to enjoy all winter long 
 
cranberry punch 
this punch can go with any party you are planning over the 
holidays use your punch bowl or pitchers serve ice in glasses so 
punch does not get watered down 
48 oz cranberry cocktail juice 
12 oz frozen orange concentrate 
2 quarts ginger ale 
1 quart orange sherbet 
2 navel oranges sliced thinly 
1 bottle burgundy wine optional 
8 oz vodka optional 
 
in a sevenquart punch bowl pour cranberry cocktail juice 
frozen orange concentrate and ginger ale 
when ready to serve add sherbet and orange slices 
add wine and vodka if desired 
 
rubyred cranberry borscht 
yield 8 cups 
8 cups water 
2 12ounce bags cranberries picked over rinsed drained and 
stems removed 
4 tablespoons unsalted butter 
3 mediumsize red onions sliced lengthwise into halfinch thick 
slices 
3 cups red cabbage about half a mediumsize head cored and 
finely sliced 
1 16ounce can small whole beets undrained 
6 tablespoons orange juice concentrate 
2 tablespoons red wine vinegar 
salt and freshly ground pepper to taste 
garnish sour cream or plain yogurt or 1 orange thinly sliced 
 
in a large casserole or kettle over medium heat bring water to 
a boil add cranberries and cook until they pop and turn shiny 
in a large skillet over medium heat melt 2 tablespoons of the 
butter add the onions and saute until translucent five to seven 
minutes add cranberries 
heat the remaining butter in another skillet add the cabbage 
and saute until limp add to the cranberry mixture stir in the 
beets with their juice orange concentrate and vinegar 
cook until thick and the cabbage and onions are incorporated 
into the soup about 15 minutes 
season with salt and pepper transfer soup to a tureen serve 
hot and garnish with sour cream yogurt or orange slices 
 
cranberry salsa 
yield 1 cup 
1 cup fresh cranberries rinsed picked over patted dry 
12 small red onion peeled and cut in chunks 
1 canned mild green chiles rinsed and seeded 
2 tablespoons cilantro or fresh dill 
2 tablespoons lime or orange juice 
1 tablespoon sugar 
 
in a food processor fitted with a metal blade combine 
cranberries onion and chile pulse on and off to make a coarse 
puree add lime or orange juice and sugar pulse on and off until 
it incorporates 
 
cranberry jubileeequals 
yield serves 8 to 12 
1 pound fresh or frozen cranberries 
12 oz red currant jelly 
14 cup sugar 
1 orange peel and cut peel into 18inch slivers 
12 cup rum 
12 cup brandy 
2 tablespoons brandy to ignite 
3 pints vanilla ice cream 
in a fourquart saucepan place fresh or defrosted cranberries 
add jelly rum brandy and orange rind 
bring to boil cook until berries pop about eight minutes keep 
some berries whole the sauce should thicken 
serve four ounces of ice cream in a goblet wine glass or glass 
dessert dish put cranberry jubliee in a silver bowl ignite with 
brandy 
serve 2 tablespoons over ice cream 
 
editors note jane weston wilson is the author of the 
lifestyle cookbook eating well when you just cant eat the way 
you used to workman publishing 
</TEXT>
