john fairfax group proprietary ltd 
which owns the sydney morning herald and three other major 
australian publications was placed into receivership monday after 
banks called in outstanding debts 
john fairfax one of australias two major newspaper groups 
along with rupert murdochs news corp ltd owes about 17 billion 
australian dollars or 131 billion to its creditors 
company officials said directors asked for the appointment of a 
provisional liquidator for the groups finance division after banks 
refused to agree to a rollover of a debt of 850 million australian 
dollars or 654 million 
the deloitte ross tohmatsu accountancy firm was then appointed 
receiver and manager at the request of john fairfax groups banking 
syndicate 
the anz bank and citibank are owed about 12 billion australian 
dollars or 850 million the remaining debt is in the form of 
highyield highrisk bonds 
john fairfax australias oldest media organization also owns 
the australian financial review business review weekly and the 
melbourne age as well as the herald in sydney the herald is the 
oldest englishlanguage newspaper in the world continuously owned 
by the same family 
in early october the company reported a net loss of 5908 
million australian dollars or 4549 million for the year ending 
june 30 
