<TEXT>
security pacific corp said today it will set 
aside 850 million to cover losses on bad loans foreclosed 
commercial real estate and the costs of closing its largely 
unprofitable merchant bank 
the bank holding company the nations fifthlargest said the 
measures would cause a loss of 320 million to 360 million during 
the fourth quarter and reduce profit for the year to 160 million 
to 200 million security pacific earned 741 million in 1989 and 
639 million in 1988 
the los angeles companys announcement follows a series of 
similar actions by big new york banks it was taken in a gloomy 
atmosphere for banks in california where softness in residential 
and commercial real estate has jeopardized what had been a huge 
profit center during the 80s boom years 
despite the actions management expects to recommend that 
security pacific maintain its quarterly dividend of 63 cents per 
share chief executive officer robert h smith said in a statement 
smith said security pacifics core consumer and commercial 
banking operations in california and the pacific northwest and its 
nationwide consumer and business finance companies remain strong 
he said taking the losses and refocussing on core businesses would 
substantially strengthen future profitability 
our objective is to directly focus our strategies and our 
resources on the areas where we can achieve solid profit growth 
smith said the overall strengths of the corporation permit us to 
take these actions at this time 
investors apparently agreed that the moves made sense bidding 
up security pacific stock by 125 to 2325 per share in midday 
trading on the new york stock exchange 
during the first three quarters security pacific already had 
increased its provisions for loan losses by 60 percent over last 
year to 541 million 
the company said it would make 600 million in additional 
loanloss reserves during the fourth quarter it also set aside 50 
million to cover the costs of a speededup program to sell off 
commercial real estate it has been stuck with through foreclosures 
security pacific said it would disband its merchant bank which 
concentrated on lending in the united kindgom and australia the 
unit which also handled commercial and investment banking and 
various securities and currency transactions said it would take a 
charge of about 200 million in the fourth quarter to cover the 
costs of disbanding 
we expect to sell downsize or completely withdraw from many 
of our european and australian activities due to dramatic and 
continuing changes in economic and financial markets smith said 
he said profitable wholesale banking units of the merchant bank 
would be incorporated into other security pacific operations 
