volkswagen plans to invest up to 63 
billion in the czechoslovak car company skoda volkswagen said 
monday after winning a bid to take over the company 
franstisek vlasak deputy premier of the czech republic told a 
news conference in prague that cooperation between the two car 
companies will begin in january 
a joint stock venture will be formed with volkswagen pumping in 
some 300 million at the start vlasak said 
ortwin witzel a volkswagen spokesman said skodas 21000 
employees were assured of no layoffs in the deal which is to begin 
with a 35 percent investment in skoda next year that will reach 70 
percent by 1995 
on sunday czechoslovakia announced that volkswagen had outbid 
renault of france and swedens volvo for skoda 
the company is considered one of the best auto manufacturers in 
eastern europe it has a long manufacturing tradition using its 
own designs and its cars have a reputation for reliability 
volkswagen said skoda will become another of vws subsidiaries 
joining audi and volkswagen in germany and seat in spain 
in the first stage beginning next year volkswagen said the 
venture will produce 200000 favoritmodel skodas by 1997 that 
number is to increase to 400000 cars a year 
skoda currently produces about 250000 cars a year 
volkswagen said it foresees a market of up to 3 million vehicles 
in the central european region by the year 2000 
volkswagen said it will modernize skodas main manufacturing 
facility in mlada boleslav and eventually build a new engine 
factory and assembly plant 
volkswagen said the motor plant is to be completed by 1995 and 
produce about 500000 engines for the czechoslovak auto industry as 
well as for other volkswagen units 
an international distribution network will also be developed to 
sell skoda cars outside europe the company said 
a contract must still be signed between the two companies and a 
new leadership named 
miroslav gregr czech minister of engineering said monday in 
prague that it may be possible to sign the basic provisions of the 
contract by the end of the year 
