take time 
the new owners hope that the wait for telephone service can be 
cut to two or three months within the next three or four years he 
told the government news agency notimex 
there are now only 55 million telephone lines in mexico serving 
a population of 81 million people france cable amp radio in 
contrast operates 28 million telephone lines in france 
shortages of lines installation costs line troubles and repair 
delays plague the telmex system 
desperate customers occasionally publish newspaper ads or write 
letters the editor in lastditch attempts to get repairs for lines 
that have been out for months 
although customers may be rejoicing at the prospect of better 
telephone service some telmex employees are unhappy at the 
privatization 
the sale agreement also provides government financing of the 
sale of 44 percent of the stock to company employees over eight 
years a dissident union leader said the privatization was carried 
out without consulting the workers 
more than 500 employees have been fired over the past two years 
and the situation of 3000 operators remains unresolved rigoberto 
barba said 
the governments privatization program is part of a revamping of 
the economy to cut the government debt and attract more foreign 
investment 
acciones y valores de mexico gte of the united states and 
telefonica de espana had offered 169 billion mexicos grupo 
gentor offered nearly 16 billion 
the sale will return telmex to the private sector formed in 
1950 by the merger of companies owned by international telephone 
and telegraph of the united states and im ericsson of sweden 
majority ownership was sold to mexicans in 1958 the government 
took over 51 percent ownership in 1972 
