lone star industries inc a large cement 
company filed monday for reorganization under federal bankruptcy 
law 
the corporation blamed its financial woes on the downturn in the 
construction industry and continued competition with subsidized 
imports 
lone stars board considred two offers from foreign investors 
and other alternatives before concluding it would be best to seek 
bankruptcy protection the company said 
more than twothirds of the cement industry in the united states 
has passed into the hands of foreign investors the company noted 
in its filing in us bankruptcy court in white plains ny 
the corporation listed assets of 1066 billion and liabilities of 
703 million as of oct 31 said company spokesman james a powers 
lone star and a number of its subsidiaries filed for 
reorganization under chapter 11 of the federal bankruptcy act lone 
star said the filing would enable it to continue a program begun in 
1989 to sell off some assets and restructure the company around its 
core business operations of cement aggregate and readymixed 
concrete 
the company took a 250 million writeoff in november 1989 as 
part of its restructuring which included a decision to sell 
marginal cement plants in pryor okla sweetwater texas and 
bonner springs kan the plants are still up for sale 
the remaining operations are located in the northeast and 
midwest 
lone star said its profits have been hurt by foreign concerns 
selling cement in the united states at less than they charge at 
home a practice known as dumping 
the federal government recently found mexican producers guilty 
of dumping 
unfortunately this ruling is several years too late lone 
star said however should other dumpers suffer the same fate 
our business could improve its profitability 
even after restructuring lone star and its affiliates retain a 
98 million ton annual cement manufacturing capacity in the united 
states the company said 
for the ninemonth period ending sept 30 lone star reported a 
net loss of 122 million or 97 cents a share net sales for the 
period were 1906 million and exclude the operations held for 
sale 
