<TEXT>
campbell soup co has sold two of its 
european businesses as part of a major restructuring to improve the 
companys financial performance the company said monday 
campbell said it sold its freshbake vegetable operations in 
the united kingdom and seafood businesses in the uk and belgium 
to albert fisher group plc for an undisclosed price the units had 
annual sales of about 150 million campbell said 
the food units were among five businesses campbell put up for 
sale in may in a move to streamline the companys operations also 
put up for sale were d lazzaroni amp c spa of italy and campbell 
irish foods ltd and mallow foods ltd of ireland 
this sale results from our strategic decision to focus our 
european efforts on branded valueadded prepared foods campbell 
chief executive officer david w johnson said in a statement 
released by the camdenbased company 
